pyhpeimc.plat.icc module¶

pyhpeimc.plat.icc.create_cfg_segment(filename, filecontent, description, auth, url)[source]¶

Takes a str into var filecontent which represents the entire content of a configuration segment, or partial configuration file. Takes a str into var description which represents the description of the configuration segment :param filename: str containing the name of the configuration segment.

Parameters:
  • filecontent – str containing the entire contents of the configuration segment
  • description – str contrianing the description of the configuration segment
  • auth – requests auth object #usually auth.creds from auth pyhpeimc.auth.class
  • url – base url of IMC RS interface #usually auth.url from pyhpeimc.auth.authclass
Returns:

If successful, Boolena of type True
Return type:

Boolean

 
>>> from pyhpeimc.auth import *

>>> from pyhpeimc.plat.icc import *

>>> auth = IMCAuth("http://", "10.101.0.203", "8080", "admin", "admin")

>>> filecontent = ("""sample file content""")
 >>> create_new_file = create_cfg_segment('CW7SNMP.cfg', filecontent, 'My New Template', auth.creds, auth.url)

>>> template_id = get_template_id('CW7SNMP.cfg', auth.creds, auth.url)

>>> assert type(template_id) is str

>>>

Parameters:
  • auth – requests auth object #usually auth.creds from auth pyhpeimc.auth.class
  • url – base url of IMC RS interface #usually auth.url from pyhpeimc.auth.authclass
Returns:

If successful, Boolean of type True
Return type:

Boolean

 
>>> from pyhpeimc.auth import *

>>> from pyhpeimc.plat.icc import *

>>> auth = IMCAuth("http://", "10.101.0.203", "8080", "admin", "admin")

>>> delete_cfg_template('CW7SNMP.cfg', auth.creds, auth.url)
True

>>> get_template_id('CW7SNMP.cfg', auth.creds, auth.url)
'template not found'
pyhpeimc.plat.icc.get_cfg_template(auth, url, folder=None)[source]¶

Function takes no input and returns a list of dictionaries containing the configuration templates in the root folder of the icc configuration template library.

Parameters:
  • auth – requests auth object #usually auth.creds from auth pyhpeimc.auth.class
  • url – base url of IMC RS interface #usually auth.url from pyhpeimc.auth.authclass
Returns:

List of Dictionaries containing folders and configuration files in the ICC library.
Return type:

list

 
>>> from pyhpeimc.auth import *

>>> from pyhpeimc.plat.icc import *

>>> auth = IMCAuth("http://", "10.101.0.203", "8080", "admin", "admin")

>>> config_templates = get_cfg_template(auth.creds, auth.url)

>>> assert type(config_templates) is list

>>> assert 'confFileName' in config_templates[0]

>>> config_templates_folder = get_cfg_template(auth.creds, auth.url, folder='ADP_Configs')

>>> assert type(config_templates_folder) is list

>>> assert 'confFileName' in config_templates_folder[0]

>>> config_template_no_folder = get_cfg_template(auth.creds, auth.url, folder='Doesnt_Exist')

>>> assert config_template_no_folder == None
